05:24.240 --> 05:25.753
Mommy!

05:28.720 --> 05:30.073
Bad dreams?

05:30.320 --> 05:33.869
- Mommy.
- All over, come on here.

05:34.880 --> 05:37.314
He's in my closet,
something's in my closet.

05:37.440 --> 05:41.194
Oh, too much junk food.
Too much of the tube, guys.

05:41.880 --> 05:43.359
He's in there.

05:43.480 --> 05:46.631
Tad, now there's nothing in this house
that's going to hurt you.

05:46.760 --> 05:48.034
Now, look what I see in the closet here.

05:48.160 --> 05:51.755
All right, I see clothing,
I see a pile of blankets on a chair,

05:51.880 --> 05:53.871
a lot of toys that weren't put away,

05:54.000 --> 05:57.913
and your favourite
over-the-hill teddy bear

05:58.040 --> 06:00.270
who would probably be a lot happier...

06:03.760 --> 06:06.877
Who would probably be a lot happier
in bed with you.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.230
And that's it, nothing else.

06:09.360 --> 06:12.557
I saw him, really. He's in the closet.

06:13.320 --> 06:17.074
He has yellow eyes,
and his mouth is about this long,

06:17.200 --> 06:20.476
and he has teeth
and they're curled like this,

06:20.600 --> 06:22.511
and he made sounds.

06:22.640 --> 06:24.358
What kind of sounds?

06:25.640 --> 06:27.358
What kind of sounds?

06:28.280 --> 06:31.158
Come on, try. What kind of sounds?
Like what?

06:35.800 --> 06:37.677
Yeah, that'd scare me pretty good.

06:37.800 --> 06:40.439
- Really.
- But he's all gone now, champ, see?

06:40.560 --> 06:42.551
He's in there, I saw him.

06:43.160 --> 06:44.354
Really.

06:44.480 --> 06:47.790
Tad, you saw him in your dreams,
in your head, nowhere else.

06:47.920 --> 06:49.273
See, Tad, there aren't any real...

06:49.400 --> 06:53.029
Tad, listen to me,
there's no such thing as real monsters.

06:53.160 --> 06:54.718
Only in stories.

06:54.840 --> 06:57.229
There's no real monsters, though.

06:58.000 --> 06:59.592
- Really?
- Really.

06:59.960 --> 07:01.109
Really.

07:02.640 --> 07:05.279
Okay, over, done with, gone, right?

07:05.400 --> 07:07.118
Over, done with, gone.

07:07.760 --> 07:09.352
Okay, snuggle in.

07:11.280 --> 07:14.716
Night, night, sleep tight,
don't let the bedbugs bite.

07:17.720 --> 07:20.075
You have good dreams, little man.

07:26.120 --> 07:28.395
There aren't any monsters, Tad.

07:39.800 --> 07:42.075
Except for the one in my closet.

07:44.080 --> 07:45.399
Please.

07:46.800 --> 07:49.678
Please, please.

08:14.520 --> 08:15.919
Hey, Tadder.

08:17.160 --> 08:19.196
You know, it looks like
someone was moving furniture around

08:19.320 --> 08:23.233
up in your bedroom last night?
Any idea on who that might have been?

08:23.600 --> 08:24.589
No.

08:25.880 --> 08:28.155
- Do you know, Donna?
- Wasn't me.

08:28.880 --> 08:30.552
Wasn't me, neither.

08:30.800 --> 08:32.073
Wasn't me.

08:33.960 --> 08:35.871
Yeah, come on in, Steve.

08:36.520 --> 08:37.748
Morning.

08:38.600 --> 08:40.431
- Mrs Trenton.
- Morning.

08:42.080 --> 08:43.558
Here you go, Tadpole.

08:43.679 --> 08:46.069
Just like I promised,
brought your horse back.

08:46.200 --> 08:49.158
- Looks pretty good stripped, doesn't it?
- Do we have a cheque for him?

08:49.280 --> 08:53.068
Listen, why don't you just wait
until I bring your table back?

08:54.000 --> 08:55.149
Thanks.

08:55.840 --> 08:58.798
Well, I can't stay
for a cup of coffee anyway.

08:59.280 --> 09:01.271
Sorry, would you like a cup?

09:01.400 --> 09:02.469
Just teasing.

09:02.600 --> 09:06.878
Hey, Tad, maybe it was Mr Kemp who
moved all your furniture around, huh?

09:07.000 --> 09:08.433
Okay.

09:08.560 --> 09:10.630
What did I do now, huh?

09:10.760 --> 09:13.752
- No, the monster did it.
- The monster?

09:13.880 --> 09:16.394
Oh, now come on,
remember what I said.

09:16.520 --> 09:19.159
"There aren't no such things
as monsters."

09:19.280 --> 09:21.840
There aren't any such things
as monsters.

09:21.960 --> 09:23.996
Not in the daytime anyway.

09:25.200 --> 09:27.714
Oh, come here, you.
"Not in the daytime."

09:27.840 --> 09:29.432
I'll show you what a monster can do
in the daytime.

09:29.560 --> 09:31.391
He grabs your knee...

09:32.560 --> 09:34.755
<i>- I know a lot about cereals...</i>
- Daddy, Daddy, look!

09:34.880 --> 09:37.678
<i>... because I'm the</i>
<i>Sharp Cereal Professor.</i>

09:38.160 --> 09:42.995
<i>Sharp Cereals, Twinkles, Coco-Bears,</i>
<i>Bran 16...</i>

09:43.120 --> 09:46.590
My daddy invented that.
He made him all up.

09:47.000 --> 09:48.035
Who?

09:48.240 --> 09:49.673
The Professor.

09:49.840 --> 09:51.910
<i>And they're good for you.</i>

09:52.600 --> 09:54.830
Well, your daddy's real smart, isn't he?

09:54.960 --> 09:57.155
As well as being
a hell of a tennis player.

09:57.280 --> 09:59.271
Ready for a rematch anytime you are.

09:59.400 --> 10:01.436
- Sure, sure.
- Tadpole.

10:01.560 --> 10:03.073
- Bye.
- Bye.

10:03.200 --> 10:04.394
Thanks.

10:07.360 --> 10:10.352
<i>No, nothing wrong here.</i>

10:15.120 --> 10:17.680
That's game, set, and match.

10:17.800 --> 10:19.119
- It was a good game.
- Oh, yeah.

10:19.240 --> 10:22.676
- What was the score, 6-0, 6-1?
- Yeah.

10:25.240 --> 10:27.879
- You're not getting tired of this, are you?
- What, are you kidding me?

10:28.000 --> 10:29.831
Getting my ass handed to me
every week? No, I love it.

10:29.960 --> 10:31.279
I'm a masochist.

10:31.400 --> 10:33.834
- Well, whatever turns you on.
- Yeah.

11:45.200 --> 11:47.794
No. Turn that off, please. It's dinner.

11:48.720 --> 11:50.073
Turn it off.

11:57.720 --> 12:01.759
This marriage is definitely
running out of conversation, isn't it?

12:08.400 --> 12:11.392
Maybe we should talk about
having another baby.

12:17.840 --> 12:19.114
I got you.

12:21.320 --> 12:24.551
Oh, no, he's got me. He's got me.

12:24.680 --> 12:26.238
Watch my chair!

12:46.640 --> 12:47.629
Hi.

12:48.920 --> 12:50.035
Excuse me.

12:50.160 --> 12:51.513
Listen, I have a problem
with my front wheel.

12:51.640 --> 12:53.232
I wonder if you could take a look at it.

12:53.360 --> 12:56.477
Park it next to the Datsun,
leave the keys in it.

12:57.520 --> 13:00.910
Well, I was kind of hoping
I could wait for it today.

13:03.640 --> 13:05.198
- You're kidding.
- No.

13:05.320 --> 13:07.754
- See you later, Harry.
- Yeah.

13:15.560 --> 13:17.755
Joe Camber will do it for you.

13:18.800 --> 13:20.153
What's that?

13:20.920 --> 13:22.194
Joe Camber.

13:22.480 --> 13:25.472
Do a real good job
and he won't rob you blind.

13:29.000 --> 13:30.672
Where's Joe Camber?

13:30.800 --> 13:34.679
You take 117 here, straight out of town,
6 miles, give or take.

13:34.800 --> 13:37.473
Go all the way out to the end,
you'll see Camber's mailbox.

13:37.600 --> 13:39.033
Can't miss it.

13:40.960 --> 13:42.109
Thanks.

13:45.240 --> 13:46.958
See you later, Harry.

14:27.960 --> 14:28.915
Hi.

14:31.480 --> 14:32.469
Pa!

14:44.720 --> 14:46.392
Tough time finding this place.
How are you?

14:46.520 --> 14:49.114
My name is Victor Trenton.
You're Mr Camber, right?

14:49.240 --> 14:50.309
Yeah.

15:04.000 --> 15:05.274
Afternoon.

15:08.280 --> 15:10.635
You folks want anything to drink?

15:11.600 --> 15:13.556
No, thank you. Thanks.

15:34.640 --> 15:35.675
Vic.

15:36.880 --> 15:39.155
Come on, Cujo. Come on, boy.

15:40.040 --> 15:42.838
Don't go over to that dog,
you don't know that dog.

15:42.960 --> 15:46.873
Don't worry about it, ma'am.
Cujo won't hurt him, he likes kids.

15:49.280 --> 15:50.235
He's safe.

15:50.360 --> 15:52.555
Run me down the hill and back,
wanna have a listen to it.

15:52.680 --> 15:54.591
- Yeah, okay.
- Vic.

15:54.760 --> 15:56.432
Oh, it's all right.

15:56.560 --> 15:58.073
Yeah, it's all right.

15:59.080 --> 16:02.356
Don't worry, Mr Trenton,
your boy will be all right.

16:15.560 --> 16:16.788
Gently.

16:17.080 --> 16:19.514
Cujo. His name's Cujo.

16:19.680 --> 16:22.956
- Cujo? How you doing, Cujo?
- He loves that.

16:23.880 --> 16:25.108
Hey, boy.

16:25.240 --> 16:27.117
What kind of dog is he?

16:27.240 --> 16:28.639
Saint Bernard.

16:28.760 --> 16:30.079
He's a great dog.

16:30.200 --> 16:32.794
Yeah, he's a pretty smart one, too.

16:37.440 --> 16:41.035
Monsters, stay out of Tad's room,
you have no business here.

16:42.320 --> 16:46.791
No monsters in Tad's closet,
it's too small for you in there. See?

16:48.440 --> 16:49.793
Where else?

16:50.080 --> 16:53.834
- Under the bed.
- Under the bed? Okay.

16:54.360 --> 16:55.509
All right.

16:55.640 --> 16:59.599
No monsters under Tad's bed,
you cannot fit under there.

17:00.720 --> 17:03.075
No monsters outside Tad's window.

17:03.800 --> 17:05.711
Can't hold on out there.

17:06.440 --> 17:08.157
Nothing will touch Tad,

17:08.480 --> 17:12.233
nothing will hurt Tad
all through this night.

17:12.560 --> 17:13.675
Okay?

17:16.079 --> 17:18.116
They have no business here.

17:23.119 --> 17:24.189
Okay?

17:35.920 --> 17:37.592
God, 1:30.

17:47.600 --> 17:48.715
What?

17:48.840 --> 17:51.752
You're just really good with him,
that's all.

17:53.600 --> 17:55.238
How am I with you?

17:55.520 --> 17:56.794
Wonderful.

17:59.640 --> 18:00.789
Night.

18:14.720 --> 18:17.553
<i>No, nothing wrong here.</i>

18:17.960 --> 18:20.269
<i>Well, that's not entirely true.</i>

18:20.400 --> 18:22.311
<i>This morning,</i>
<i>thousands of people across the country</i>

18:22.440 --> 18:25.750
<i>reported internal haemorrhaging</i>
<i>after eating Sharp Cereal products.</i>

18:25.880 --> 18:27.836
<i>The scare, however,</i>
<i>proved to be a false alarm.</i>

18:27.960 --> 18:29.359
- Hi.
- Hi.

18:29.480 --> 18:31.038
- Hi, Tad.
- Hi, Dad.

18:31.160 --> 18:34.470
<i>Despite that fact, the scare has reached</i>
<i>alarming proportions.</i>

18:34.600 --> 18:37.558
<i>Sharp Cereal has been unavailable</i>
<i>for comment.</i>

18:38.160 --> 18:40.435
<i>Nope, nothing wrong here, folks.</i>

18:40.560 --> 18:41.629
Cute.

18:43.520 --> 18:45.511
That's our ad campaign.

18:45.640 --> 18:47.278
They've recalled
the whole goddamn cereal.

18:47.400 --> 18:49.516
- Then there's no harm done, is there?
- "No harm done"?

18:49.640 --> 18:51.596
Donna, that guy comes into
America's living room,

18:51.720 --> 18:53.312
and he says to kids, he says,
"Trust me."

18:53.440 --> 18:55.351
- Yes, I understand.
- No, I don't think you do.

18:55.480 --> 18:57.152
You see, we created that guy,
Roger and me.

18:57.280 --> 18:58.998
- He's our brainchild.
- Yes, I understand.

18:59.120 --> 19:01.395
And these kids,
they go out and they buy the cereal.

19:01.520 --> 19:03.431
All the Sharp Cereals. All of them.

19:03.600 --> 19:07.593
Bran 16, All Grain,
Coco-Bears, Twinkles.

19:07.720 --> 19:12.111
And now, kids all over the country
are peeing and puking red dye

19:12.240 --> 19:15.789
and scaring the hell out of their parents,
and we told them to buy it.

19:15.920 --> 19:19.629
The Sharp Professor is us.
That's our ass, Roger's and mine.

19:19.760 --> 19:21.876
You'll work it out,
you always have before.

19:22.000 --> 19:23.797
All right, look,
I appreciate this isn't a world crisis,

19:23.920 --> 19:26.514
- it's not a mass suicide...
- That'll be Roger.

19:26.640 --> 19:27.755
Hello?

19:27.880 --> 19:30.394
Yeah, sure, Roger, hold on. It's Roger.

19:30.520 --> 19:31.555
Calm down.

19:36.360 --> 19:37.509
Hi, Rog.

19:37.640 --> 19:39.835
Roger, Rog, calm down.

19:40.200 --> 19:43.476
Calm down, we'll work it out,
we always have before.

19:44.440 --> 19:45.998
Well, then, nobody got hurt, right?

19:46.120 --> 19:48.236
What we're talking about here
is a lot of scared people.

19:48.360 --> 19:50.351
<i>We're talking about recalling</i>
<i>the whole goddamn cereal.</i>

19:50.480 --> 19:53.552
Well, that's not too bad.
I mean, it certainly could be worse.

19:53.680 --> 19:56.911
Hey, buddy, don't yell at me,
I didn't do it, it's your dye not my...

19:57.040 --> 19:57.995
Roger.

19:58.120 --> 20:01.112
<i>...like there's nothing wrong here.</i>
- Look, look, no harm was done,

20:01.240 --> 20:04.437
and I'm sure given time,
this whole thing will blow over...

20:04.560 --> 20:06.949
<i>We're having a special board meeting</i>
<i>next week, okay?</i>

20:07.080 --> 20:08.035
Special board meeting?

20:08.160 --> 20:09.991
<i>To re-assess our position</i>
<i>re the Professor.</i>

20:10.120 --> 20:11.075
Sure, we can be there.

20:11.200 --> 20:12.553
<i>- You better be there.</i>
- Right.

20:12.680 --> 20:14.511
<i>You better start taking this</i>
<i>a little more seriously, too.</i>

20:14.640 --> 20:16.551
- Right.
<i>- I'm not kidding.</i>

20:18.040 --> 20:21.032
"To re-assess our position,
re the Professor."

20:23.160 --> 20:25.151
We lost the Sharp account.

20:32.280 --> 20:33.395
Brett!

21:37.400 --> 21:38.389
Hi.

21:39.360 --> 21:40.395
Hi.

21:40.840 --> 21:42.114
Come here.

21:43.320 --> 21:45.470
Can't see you anymore, Steve.

21:47.400 --> 21:50.233
Well, it's a little late for that, isn't it?

21:50.800 --> 21:52.995
Just came by to tell you that.

21:57.360 --> 22:00.272
Okay. Look, can you tell me why?

22:03.560 --> 22:04.515
Jesus, I don't know.

22:04.640 --> 22:06.790
I got this terrific husband
and this terrific kid

22:06.920 --> 22:09.718
and here I am screwing around
with the local stud.

22:09.840 --> 22:11.558
No offence intended.

22:11.680 --> 22:12.999
None taken.

22:13.520 --> 22:14.953
What the hell's the matter?

22:15.120 --> 22:17.918
It's just over, that's all. I want it over.

22:18.280 --> 22:22.558
It's not your fault.
It was just a stupid mistake.

22:25.960 --> 22:27.029
Okay.

22:27.840 --> 22:29.478
Whatever you want.

22:35.520 --> 22:36.794
I'm sorry.

24:04.240 --> 24:06.674
- Hi, pumpkin.
- Hi. Look what I made.

24:06.800 --> 24:09.394
Hey, that's really nice.

24:09.520 --> 24:11.715
What happened to you?

24:11.840 --> 24:15.389
- Nothing.
- Yeah? Doesn't look like nothing.

24:15.520 --> 24:17.795
I got hit by a swing.

24:18.360 --> 24:20.237
Come here, let me make it better.

24:23.120 --> 24:25.076
Well, over, done with, gone, right?

24:25.200 --> 24:26.315
Over, done with, gone.

24:26.440 --> 24:27.919
Okay, strap in.

24:42.400 --> 24:45.153
- Oh, you like this, huh?
- It's fun.

24:48.960 --> 24:50.552
<i>Bum, bum, bum</i>

24:50.680 --> 24:54.798
<i>- I see your hiney, nice and shiny</i>
<i>- Nice and shiny</i>

24:54.920 --> 24:58.549
<i>- lf you don't hide it, I think I'll bite it</i>
<i>- I think I'll bite it</i>

25:00.760 --> 25:03.672
- Daddy's home.
- Yeah, so I see.

25:05.320 --> 25:07.390
Okay, everybody out.

25:09.160 --> 25:10.752
- Hi.
- Daddy!

25:11.400 --> 25:12.753
My big guy.

25:14.120 --> 25:15.917
- Home early, huh?
- Yeah.

25:16.800 --> 25:19.360
- What happened to your head?
- Fell off the swing.

25:19.480 --> 25:21.232
- You did?
- Pinto's doing that thing again.

25:21.360 --> 25:22.918
I'll have to take it out to Camber's.
Let me see.

25:23.040 --> 25:24.632
- Yeah, I've heard that one before.
- Come here.

25:24.760 --> 25:26.318
Hey, would you like to play
some baseball?

25:26.440 --> 25:27.395
- Yeah.
- Would you?

25:27.520 --> 25:29.954
There's a load of groceries here, Tad,
that's your job.

25:30.880 --> 25:32.359
No, not today.

25:32.520 --> 25:35.512
Go on, go get your mitt,
you left it on the front lawn again.

25:35.640 --> 25:36.755
- Go on.
- Okay.

25:40.240 --> 25:42.117
So what'd you do today?

25:42.960 --> 25:47.476
Oh, you know, the usual.
Groceries, errands.

25:49.240 --> 25:50.309
Yeah?

25:50.840 --> 25:52.558
Roger come in today?

25:52.680 --> 25:55.478
No, he's still in mourning
for the account.

26:51.520 --> 26:53.351
What the hell is that?

26:53.480 --> 26:55.038
It's an engine hoist.

26:56.960 --> 27:00.430
You wanted one.
It's the new hydraulic hoist you wanted.

27:01.280 --> 27:03.077
You kept telling me you need one.

27:03.200 --> 27:05.509
You tell me
what the fuck you're up to, Charity.

27:05.640 --> 27:07.835
Sit down and eat, and I will.

27:08.640 --> 27:10.278
Can't you use it?

27:12.160 --> 27:14.151
Damn well can't afford it.

27:32.200 --> 27:33.838
I won the lottery.

27:43.000 --> 27:44.319
$5,000.

27:48.400 --> 27:50.038
When do we get it?

27:51.320 --> 27:53.276
Two weeks, a little less.

27:58.160 --> 27:59.309
Thanks.

28:01.000 --> 28:02.752
I got you a present.

28:03.800 --> 28:05.995
You give me one, Joe. Okay?

28:10.440 --> 28:13.591
I wanna go away for a week with Brett,

28:14.720 --> 28:16.995
to see my sister in Connecticut.

28:22.240 --> 28:26.279
Boston? What the hell
are you gonna do in Boston?

28:27.200 --> 28:29.873
What makes you think
I could afford to go, anyways?

28:30.720 --> 28:32.438
Shit, you're rolling in it!

28:32.680 --> 28:35.752
You might have to dig out something
from the mattress is all.

28:36.760 --> 28:39.228
You're kicking up your heels a little,
aren't you, Joey?

28:39.360 --> 28:42.397
You gonna go right to the Combat Zone,
see a couple of dirty movies

28:42.520 --> 28:43.589
and try to get the clap.

28:43.720 --> 28:46.917
You better look out, Pervier,
or I'll sic my dog on you.

28:47.680 --> 28:48.669
That dog?

28:48.800 --> 28:51.439
You couldn't sic that dog on me
if I was coming at you

28:51.560 --> 28:53.994
with a straight razor in each hand.

28:55.040 --> 28:57.076
What's your wife say about it?

28:57.200 --> 28:59.031
She don't know, she don't have to know.

28:59.160 --> 29:00.434
Oh, sure.

29:01.040 --> 29:04.032
She gonna take the boy and visit
her sister. Gonna be gone a week.

29:09.040 --> 29:12.191
You gonna spend a lump
of that lottery money, huh?

29:12.360 --> 29:16.239
- Oh, shit.
- Broads, booze, baseball!

29:16.680 --> 29:19.831
I don't want to do it alone,
it's no fun. Come on.

29:22.600 --> 29:24.716
I don't give a shit if I do.

29:26.440 --> 29:29.432
Okay, now you're talking.
Now you're talking!

30:04.320 --> 30:06.914
You got me, got me!
You got me, got me!

30:07.640 --> 30:08.709
How's my boy, huh?

30:08.840 --> 30:10.034
You having a good time
at summer camp?

30:10.160 --> 30:11.559
- No.
- No?

30:12.320 --> 30:14.754
Your mom said you were having fun.

30:16.240 --> 30:18.037
- Come on, you wanna go home, then?
- Yeah.

30:18.160 --> 30:20.720
All right, come on, let's go.
Over the shoulders.

30:20.840 --> 30:22.717
Yeah, home we go.

30:22.840 --> 30:24.796
Think you can beat me to the Jaguar?

30:24.920 --> 30:26.797
Think you can beat me? Come on.

31:01.080 --> 31:03.514
God, you scared the shit out of me.

31:03.640 --> 31:04.914
I'm sorry.

31:06.160 --> 31:07.912
How'd you get in here anyway?

31:08.120 --> 31:09.917
Finished with your table,
I brought it back.

31:10.040 --> 31:13.316
It's all stripped
and it's a beautiful piece of work.

31:13.440 --> 31:15.351
Leave it on the back porch.

31:15.480 --> 31:16.913
