Mommy don't know them.

33:56.480 --> 33:57.674
Come here.

34:04.600 --> 34:06.272
You see, Tad,

34:07.280 --> 34:10.875
the thing about the monster words
is they're written down.

34:11.400 --> 34:13.277
Yeah, that's the only way
your dad can know them.

34:13.400 --> 34:16.312
So, what I'll do is I'll copy them for you

34:16.440 --> 34:19.955
and I'll tack them on your bedroom wall
and that way...

34:20.080 --> 34:22.913
Well, your mom
can read them to you every night.

34:23.040 --> 34:24.234
Will you?

34:24.360 --> 34:27.351
I will. I promise I'll do it for you tonight.

34:29.960 --> 34:32.110
Okay, Tad, time for your nap.

34:33.679 --> 34:35.351
I love you, sport.

34:40.960 --> 34:42.473
Did you fix it?

34:43.000 --> 34:44.433
No, I don't have the tools.

34:44.560 --> 34:47.472
Take it up to Joe Camber's,
it's only 7 miles.

34:47.600 --> 34:48.998
Yeah, maybe.

34:49.400 --> 34:51.594
I'll try and run it up Saturday
if I can get the time.

34:51.719 --> 34:53.995
It's okay, I'll take care of it.

36:18.040 --> 36:19.598
Cujo?

36:42.800 --> 36:44.358
Cujo.

36:46.640 --> 36:48.596
Cujo, what's the matter?

36:51.160 --> 36:52.957
Cujo, it's me, Brett.

36:55.640 --> 36:57.312
Take it easy, boy.

36:59.200 --> 37:01.077
I'm not gonna hurt you.

37:04.600 --> 37:05.794
Cujo?

37:13.640 --> 37:14.868
Cujo!

37:16.680 --> 37:17.999
Cujo!

37:36.960 --> 37:40.157
I don't want you to go for 10 days.
I want you to go for one day.

37:40.280 --> 37:44.319
Tad, I'll be back before you know it.
Now give me a kiss, come on.

37:50.080 --> 37:52.799
I forgot to take the Pinto into Camber's.

37:54.600 --> 37:56.352
I'll take care of it.

38:02.280 --> 38:04.111
Well, I'll see you.

38:09.000 --> 38:10.718
Vic! Stay there.

38:24.640 --> 38:26.517
I just wanted you to know it was over.

38:26.640 --> 38:29.359
I just wanted to be sure
that you knew that.

38:30.400 --> 38:33.153
I can't make that it never happened, Vic.

38:33.760 --> 38:35.512
I can't make like
it never happened either, Donna.

38:35.640 --> 38:37.358
I know. I know that.

38:38.080 --> 38:40.799
So I don't know what I'm gonna do yet.

38:47.120 --> 38:48.519
I don't know.

39:09.040 --> 39:11.315
Get the rest of the bags, Brett.

39:21.880 --> 39:22.949
Mom?

39:23.960 --> 39:26.190
You know, I'm worried about Cujo.

39:26.320 --> 39:29.756
I saw him this morning in the fog
and he was all bloody.

39:29.920 --> 39:32.354
He was dripping foam at the mouth.

39:32.480 --> 39:34.232
I think I better tell Dad.

39:34.360 --> 39:36.351
No, you do no such thing.

39:36.640 --> 39:39.029
Your father would just
jump on something like that.

39:39.160 --> 39:41.355
You just leave him be and he'll come
mooching around your dad

39:41.480 --> 39:43.198
and your dad will take care of him.

39:43.600 --> 39:45.079
He loves Cujo.

39:45.200 --> 39:47.156
Yeah, I guess he would.

39:47.280 --> 39:50.397
Tell you what,
we'll call your father tonight.

39:50.960 --> 39:55.112
When you talk to him,
you say, sort of casually,

39:57.040 --> 39:59.190
"You feeding my dog, Daddy?"

40:00.120 --> 40:01.553
Then you know.

40:01.960 --> 40:03.393
- Yeah.
- Brett!

41:05.280 --> 41:06.429
Cujo.

41:07.760 --> 41:09.716
What're you growling at?

41:33.120 --> 41:36.590
Come on! Come on! I don't give a shit!

41:36.720 --> 41:39.439
You hear me? I don't give a shit!

41:48.120 --> 41:51.795
You are dead, you stupid son of a bitch.

42:47.240 --> 42:48.468
Cujo!

42:50.760 --> 42:51.829
Cujo!

42:57.720 --> 42:58.994
Cujo!

43:01.640 --> 43:02.755
Shit.

43:29.960 --> 43:31.075
Gary!

43:35.120 --> 43:36.439
Hey, Gary!

43:56.240 --> 43:57.355
Gary?

44:06.000 --> 44:07.149
Gary!

44:18.520 --> 44:21.080
Oh. Shit.

44:22.520 --> 44:23.919
Gary.

44:24.840 --> 44:26.034
Gary.

45:25.160 --> 45:26.275
Cujo!

45:29.360 --> 45:31.157
Oh, my God, you're rabid.

45:35.080 --> 45:37.230
Easy, boy. Easy, Cujo.

45:50.480 --> 45:53.711
<i>- One rolled over and the other one said</i>
<i>- One rolled over and the other one said</i>

45:53.840 --> 45:54.795
<i>Bum, bum, bum</i>

45:54.920 --> 45:59.072
<i>- I see your hiney, it's nice and shiny</i>
<i>- I see your hiney, it's nice and shiny</i>

45:59.200 --> 46:03.751
<i>- lf you don't hide it, I think I'll bite it</i>
<i>- lf you don't hide it, I think I'll bite it</i>

46:10.160 --> 46:13.835
<i>Oh, my goodness, oh, my soul!</i>

46:22.320 --> 46:25.869
Come on, baby. Just a little more to go.

47:03.520 --> 47:08.275
- Well, I think we've arrived, Tadder.
- Yeah, but is anybody home?

47:09.120 --> 47:11.076
I don't know, we'll see.

47:16.080 --> 47:17.229
Hello?

47:22.240 --> 47:24.754
- I can't get my seatbelt off.
- Hello?

47:29.920 --> 47:32.388
Just great. This is great.

47:36.160 --> 47:40.278
- I can't get my dang old seatbelt off.
- All right! I'm coming.

47:41.880 --> 47:43.791
You're so impatient.

47:44.960 --> 47:46.598
Damn belt is stuck again.

47:46.720 --> 47:49.598
I guess everything in this car is broken.

47:49.720 --> 47:52.234
I wish Daddy'd get a new car.

47:52.360 --> 47:53.998
Sounds good to me.

47:56.080 --> 47:57.559
Damn this car.

47:57.680 --> 47:59.477
You pull while I push.

48:02.400 --> 48:04.152
Oh, I can't get it.

48:04.280 --> 48:05.235
Pull!

48:43.320 --> 48:45.629
- It's okay, it's okay.
- Mommy!

48:52.800 --> 48:55.314
Oh, there's no monsters.

48:56.880 --> 48:58.313
I know, baby.

48:58.440 --> 49:01.079
It's the monster out of my closet!

49:01.200 --> 49:04.670
Listen to me, it's not a monster,
it's just a doggy.

49:28.160 --> 49:31.072
Okay, okay.

49:31.200 --> 49:32.155
I want to go home.

49:32.280 --> 49:33.952
The doggy's gone.
See, the doggy's gone.

49:35.000 --> 49:37.230
Okay, all right, we're gonna go home
right now.

49:37.880 --> 49:39.233
We're going right now.

49:43.360 --> 49:44.839
Damn this car!

49:48.120 --> 49:50.554
- I want to go home.
- Listen to me!

49:50.680 --> 49:53.513
- I want to go home.
- We can't go home right now, okay?

49:53.880 --> 49:55.598
We have to wait.

49:56.280 --> 49:58.874
Tad, we have to let... Okay.

49:59.000 --> 50:01.560
We have to let the engine die down.

50:02.960 --> 50:03.915
Okay.

50:06.440 --> 50:09.273
Okay, we're gonna go home
in a few minutes.

50:12.840 --> 50:15.229
We're gonna go home in a few minutes.

51:08.240 --> 51:10.037
Mom, aren't we going?

51:11.320 --> 51:12.275
Ma!

51:14.760 --> 51:16.671
Yeah, okay, we'll try it.

51:18.200 --> 51:19.872
Cross your fingers.

51:20.280 --> 51:22.350
Come on, baby, one more time.

51:28.240 --> 51:32.313
Great, it started! We're gonna go home.

51:44.040 --> 51:45.758
Fuck you, dog.

52:06.640 --> 52:08.631
Come on, damn it, turn over.

52:11.040 --> 52:13.508
Goddamn you, car!

52:15.000 --> 52:17.833
God, why didn't you get this car fixed?

52:19.280 --> 52:20.235
God!

52:25.120 --> 52:27.429
Mommy, are you okay?

52:30.880 --> 52:31.995
Yeah.

52:32.760 --> 52:34.955
I thought you were mad at me.

52:37.480 --> 52:39.357
No, baby, never at you.

52:45.560 --> 52:47.391
Can he get us in here?

52:51.680 --> 52:52.635
No.

52:54.560 --> 52:57.996
Can he eat his way in here? Can he?

52:59.080 --> 53:00.115
No.

53:02.160 --> 53:03.832
Wish he would die.

53:05.720 --> 53:06.948
Me, too.

54:18.240 --> 54:19.992
Mommy?

54:20.360 --> 54:23.318
- What?
- I gotta go pee.

54:23.760 --> 54:27.196
- Oh, Tadder, you got to go bad?
- Yes.

54:27.800 --> 54:29.074
Real bad?

54:32.280 --> 54:36.034
Okay, look, we're gonna open this door
just a little crack, okay?

54:36.160 --> 54:38.037
And you pee right outside here.

54:41.000 --> 54:42.319
Why can't we go outside?

54:42.440 --> 54:45.000
Because it's too cold.
Get your pants down.

54:45.120 --> 54:46.792
- Ready?
- Ready.

54:46.920 --> 54:48.751
Okay, go quick.

55:08.440 --> 55:10.192
Zip up your pants, Tad.

57:34.960 --> 57:39.033
- Don't open the window!
- Got to open a little bit for some air.

57:44.160 --> 57:45.593
What's that?

57:45.720 --> 57:47.233
The monster words.

57:47.360 --> 57:49.954
Oh, let me see. Please?

57:50.600 --> 57:52.556
I'll give them right back.

57:54.000 --> 57:57.072
- Something to drink.
- Oh, baby.

57:58.320 --> 58:01.630
We got just a little bit left
and I think we ought to save it, okay?

58:01.760 --> 58:03.671
Can you wait just for a while?

58:03.800 --> 58:05.836
- Yeah.
- Good, thank you.

58:07.720 --> 58:10.109
Can I have my monster words back?

58:12.920 --> 58:17.471
"Monsters stay out of Tad's room.
You have no business here.

58:17.920 --> 58:22.471
"No monsters under Tad's bed,
you can't fit under there.

58:23.280 --> 58:28.195
"No monsters hiding in Tad's closet,
it's too small in there.

58:28.760 --> 58:31.911
"No monsters outside Tad's window,

58:32.040 --> 58:34.952
"you can't hold on out there.

58:35.240 --> 58:39.233
"No vampires, no werewolves,
nothing that bites.

58:39.360 --> 58:42.477
"You have no business here."

58:43.960 --> 58:46.235
Maybe it'll start now.

58:47.160 --> 58:50.436
I'm afraid to try it because
the battery's so weak.

58:52.000 --> 58:54.514
What does it matter
if the battery's weak or not?

58:54.640 --> 58:56.392
We're just sitting here.

58:56.520 --> 58:57.714
Try it.

58:58.760 --> 58:59.988
Please.

59:01.640 --> 59:02.709
Okay.

59:17.240 --> 59:18.468
Told you.

59:22.880 --> 59:26.236
Don't worry, when the mailman comes
we'll go home.

59:36.880 --> 59:39.394
- Just lay them out like this.
- Okay.

59:42.280 --> 59:43.952
- George.
- Yeah.

59:45.520 --> 59:49.832
Hold mail until notified, the Cambers,
remember, George?

59:49.960 --> 59:51.757
My mind's gone.

59:51.880 --> 59:54.235
Thanks, Roger. Saved me a trip.

01:00:12.680 --> 01:00:14.955
Get back in that barn, damn you.

01:00:50.320 --> 01:00:51.639
Oh, my God.

01:01:27.120 --> 01:01:29.031
It makes him angry.

01:01:49.560 --> 01:01:52.154
Come on. Please be quiet.

01:01:59.880 --> 01:02:02.189
I want to go home. I want to go home.

01:02:02.320 --> 01:02:04.959
Momma wants to go home
very much, too.

01:02:06.240 --> 01:02:09.073
Can we please go home?

01:02:09.200 --> 01:02:10.428
Oh, baby.

01:02:13.120 --> 01:02:16.237
<i>No, nothing wrong here.</i>

01:02:24.000 --> 01:02:26.958
<i>- No, nothing wrong here.</i>
- This is ridiculous.

01:02:27.120 --> 01:02:30.795
We need a whole new campaign.
Start from scratch, huh, Vic?

01:02:32.760 --> 01:02:34.830
- Vic?
- Huh, what? I'm sorry.

01:02:34.960 --> 01:02:37.428
Cut it, Frank. We're wasting our time.

01:02:38.440 --> 01:02:40.954
- Where you going?
- I need some sugar.

01:02:58.040 --> 01:02:59.155
Tadder?

01:03:00.600 --> 01:03:01.669
Tad?

01:04:10.480 --> 01:04:11.469
Oh, shit.

01:06:59.800 --> 01:07:01.950
Mommy, Mommy.

01:07:03.160 --> 01:07:04.639
Mommy, please!

01:07:04.760 --> 01:07:07.479
Mommy!

01:07:08.520 --> 01:07:11.080
- I want to go home.
- Okay, baby.

01:07:12.840 --> 01:07:14.956
Real soon.

01:07:15.080 --> 01:07:18.868
Real soon, dear. Tadder, real soon.

01:07:19.000 --> 01:07:20.911
I want to go home.

01:07:21.040 --> 01:07:23.679
Don't get out of the car.

01:07:41.120 --> 01:07:42.314
No!

01:07:53.480 --> 01:07:55.755
- Do you have any idea what time it is?
- Just wanted you to know, Roger.

01:07:55.880 --> 01:07:58.189
- I have to go back.
- Go back? Go home?

01:07:58.320 --> 01:07:59.912
You can't do that.
This whole damn thing was your idea.

01:08:00.040 --> 01:08:02.429
- You can't do that to me.
- I know, Roger. I'm sorry.

01:08:02.560 --> 01:08:04.755
- But I can't stay.
- Oh, look, I understand.

01:08:04.880 --> 01:08:06.757
I know what you're going through.

01:08:06.880 --> 01:08:08.632
- You do?
- Of course.

01:08:08.800 --> 01:08:10.438
You think I'm so wrapped up
in my own problems,

01:08:10.560 --> 01:08:13.313
I can't see what's happening to you.
I see it, believe me.

01:08:13.440 --> 01:08:15.670
- Happens to everyone.
- Not to me, it doesn't.

01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:17.995
Oh, you can't come up with an answer
to the Sharp account

01:08:18.120 --> 01:08:21.270
so you think you're through,
you think the creative juice is gone.

01:08:21.399 --> 01:08:24.118
It's panic, that's all. Just panic.

01:08:28.240 --> 01:08:31.868
Hey, what did I say?
Vic, what is eating you?

01:08:35.160 --> 01:08:36.991
Donna's been having an affair.

01:08:38.760 --> 01:08:41.558
Before I left she told me she had quit it.

01:08:41.680 --> 01:08:44.671
But, Roger, she hasn't
answered the phone in two days.

01:08:44.800 --> 01:08:46.198
Oh, shit.

01:08:46.399 --> 01:08:48.118
I'm going back.

01:08:48.720 --> 01:08:50.038
I'm sorry.

01:08:50.279 --> 01:08:53.795
Look, maybe she's spending
the night with a friend.

01:08:53.920 --> 01:08:56.434
Oh, I can't believe I said that.
Call someone.

01:08:56.560 --> 01:08:58.470
Call the police,
have them go over and take a look.

01:08:58.600 --> 01:09:00.430
That's not the point.

01:09:00.560 --> 01:09:03.916
God damn it, Vic,
you can't run out on the Sharp account.

01:09:04.160 --> 01:09:05.639
Wanna bet?

01:10:10.000 --> 01:10:12.309
Please, God, get me out of here.

01:10:15.160 --> 01:10:17.196
Please get me out of here.

01:10:54.120 --> 01:10:55.189
Tad.

01:10:57.960 --> 01:10:59.473
Tadder, wake up.

01:11:01.600 --> 01:11:02.669
Tad.

01:11:06.360 --> 01:11:08.157
Tad! Tad!

01:11:09.680 --> 01:11:10.795
Tad!

01:11:10.960 --> 01:11:12.359
Oh, my God.

01:11:12.840 --> 01:11:14.193
Tad, wake up.

01:11:16.600 --> 01:11:18.352
Oh, come on.

01:11:26.040 --> 01:11:28.190
Breathe, breathe.

01:11:29.960 --> 01:11:30.915
Tad.

01:11:36.760 --> 01:11:38.751
Come on, breathe. Breathe.

01:11:38.880 --> 01:11:40.916
Breathe, breathe, breathe.

01:11:41.040 --> 01:11:41.995
Come on.

01:11:43.040 --> 01:11:45.474
Tadder, talk to me.

01:11:45.600 --> 01:11:47.397
I want to go home.

01:11:49.040 --> 01:11:50.314
- Tadder, talk.
- I want to go home.

01:11:50.440 --> 01:11:52.829
<i>Four little monkeys sitting on a bed</i>

01:11:52.960 --> 01:11:54.916
<i>- One rolled over</i>
<i>- One rolled over</i>

01:11:55.040 --> 01:11:57.429
<i>- and the other one said</i>
<i>- Bum, bum, bum</i>

01:11:57.560 --> 01:12:00.438
<i>I see your hiney, nice and shiny</i>

01:12:01.640 --> 01:12:04.632
<i>If you don't hide it, I think I'll bite it</i>

01:12:05.280 --> 01:12:06.235
Okay.

01:12:21.960 --> 01:12:23.393
Anybody home?

01:12:29.800 --> 01:12:30.949
Donna?

01:12:53.560 --> 01:12:54.754
Donna?

01:13:30.280 --> 01:13:33.636
We got to everybody on that list,
didn't we, Bannerman?

01:13:33.760 --> 01:13:36.354
Did we ever reach Mrs...
What was her name?

01:13:36.480 --> 01:13:39.790
- Her friend in Werdon?
- I said yes.

01:13:39.920 --> 01:13:44.277
Man, I'm telling you, it was Kemp.
All right? This was Kemp who did this.

01:13:44.760 --> 01:13:48.435
- Where's your wife's car, Mr Trenton?
- The what?

01:13:49.000 --> 01:13:53.039
It bothers me. Kemp came here, right?
He grabs your wife and son.

01:13:53.160 --> 01:13:56.914
Why? Well, he's crazy,
which is reason enough.

01:13:57.240 --> 01:13:58.912
Where's her car?

01:13:59.040 --> 01:14:01.554
It's in the shop at Camber's.
The needle valve is sticking.

01:14:01.680 --> 01:14:03.352
- Joe Camber's?
- Yes, Joe Camber's.

01:14:03.480 --> 01:14:05.391
- She was going to take it in.
- When would that have been?

01:14:05.520 --> 01:14:07.875
- I don't know.
- I'll check it out.

01:14:09.440 --> 01:14:12.796
Wait, what are you going
to do about Kemp?

01:14:12.920 --> 01:14:15.832
We've got an MV alert out on him,
we'll pick him up soon enough.

01:14:15.960 --> 01:14:17.757
Kemp is taken care of.

01:16:35.000 --> 01:16:36.433
Goddamn you!

01:16:56.800 --> 01:16:57.755
No!

01:17:15.320 --> 01:17:19.359
Oh, Tad. Oh, not now!

01:17:19.760 --> 01:17:23.639
Oh, please, not now.
Oh, please, please.

01:17:26.120 --> 01:17:27.314
Breathe!

01:17:27.480 --> 01:17:28.913
Not now!

01:17:29.720 --> 01:17:30.994
I want...

01:17:31.920 --> 01:17:34.275
- I want my daddy.
